    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "James",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 1,
        "summary": "If any of you lack wisdom, let him ask of God\u2014Resist temptation\u2014Be doers of the word\u2014James explains how to recognize pure religion.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "James, a servant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, to the twelve tribes which are scattered abroad, greeting.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Servant.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Twelve Tribes of.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "My brethren, count it all joy when ye fall into divers temptations;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0James 1:2 \u2026 many afflictions;",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Temptation.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Knowing this, that the trying of your faith worketh patience.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0approval by trial. TG\u00a0Opposition; Test.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Patience.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But let patience have her perfect work, that ye may be perfect and entire, wanting nothing.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Perfection.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 25
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "If any of you lack wisdom, let him ask of God, that giveth to all men liberally, and upbraideth not; and it shall be given him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:68; JS\u2014H 1:11.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Guidance, Divine; Learn; Wisdom.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Benevolence; Revelation.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 58
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0reproaches, censures.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But let him ask in faith, nothing wavering. For he that wavereth is like a wave of the sea driven with the wind and tossed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0doubting, hesitating. TG\u00a0Doubt.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For let not that man think that he shall receive any thing of the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A double minded man is unstable in all his ways.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 18:21; Ps. 12:2; Hosea 10:2. TG\u00a0Integrity.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Let the brother of low degree rejoice in that he is exalted:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 23:12.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But the rich, in that he is made low: because as the flower of the grass he shall pass away.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 40:6\u20138.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the sun is no sooner risen with a burning heat, but it withereth the grass, and the flower thereof falleth, and the grace of the fashion of it perisheth: so also shall the rich man fade away in his ways.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0beauty of its appearance.",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 125
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 6:17 (17\u201319).",
                        "start": 176,
                        "end": 180
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Blessed is the man that endureth temptation: for when he is tried, he shall receive the crown of life, which the Lord hath promised to them that love him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Pet. 3:14. TG\u00a0Blessing.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0James 1:12 \u2026 resisteth temptation \u2026 TG\u00a0Steadfastness.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Test.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Exaltation; Reward.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Let no man say when he is tempted, I am tempted of God: for God cannot be tempted with evil, neither tempteth he any man:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Perfection of.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Evil.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But every man is tempted, when he is drawn away of his own lust, and enticed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Temptation.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastity; Lust; Motivations; Sensuality.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Then when lust hath conceived, it bringeth forth sin: and sin, when it is finished, bringeth forth death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Do not err, my beloved brethren.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and cometh down from the Father of lights, with whom is no variableness, neither shadow of turning.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 85:12.",
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moro. 7:12 (12\u201313).",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 3:27; 2\u00a0Cor. 9:15. TG\u00a0God, Gifts of.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 67:9.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 67:4, 9.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 85
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Perfection of.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Of his own will begat he us with the word of truth, that we should be a kind of firstfruits of his creatures.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, my beloved brethren, let every man be swift to hear, slow to speak, slow to wrath:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 17:27.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Patience.",
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Anger.",
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p19",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the wrath of man worketh not the righteousness of God.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore lay apart all filthiness and superfluity of naughtiness, and receive with meekness the engrafted word, which is able to save your souls.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Filthiness.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0overabundance of malice, trouble, evil.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Meek.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 92
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0implanted, ingrafted.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But be ye doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving your own selves.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Commitment; Duty; Good Works; Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For if any be a hearer of the word, and not a doer, he is like unto a man beholding his natural face in a glass:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 6:49 (47\u201349).",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 13:12.",
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 111
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For he beholdeth himself, and goeth his way, and straightway forgetteth what manner of man he was.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But whoso looketh into the perfect law of liberty, and continueth therein, he being not a forgetful hearer, but a doer of the work, this man shall be blessed in his deed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Law of.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Liberty.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "If any man among you seem to be religious, and bridleth not his tongue, but deceiveth his own heart, this man's religion is vain.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip; Profanity.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0useless, deceptive, erroneous.",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Pure religion and undefiled before God and the Father is this, To visit the fatherless and widows in their affliction, and to keep himself unspotted from the world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Charity.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 44:6. TG\u00a0Benevolence; Good Works; Welfare.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 26:13; Job 22:9; 31:21 (21\u201322); Ps. 10:14; 146:9 (1\u201310); 3\u00a0Ne. 24:5; D&C 136:8 (7\u20139).",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 86
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Widows.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 97
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Affliction.",
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 117
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 5:22; 1\u00a0Jn. 5:18; D&C 59:9. TG\u00a0Chastity.",
                        "start": 139,
                        "end": 148
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0James 1:27 \u2026 the vices of the world.",
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 157
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worldliness.",
                        "start": 158,
                        "end": 163
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 119,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}